6:
Wouldn't it be faster to just bust this
thing open?
10:
We need to be cautious. A chest
from the ruins like this could hold all
matter of dangers within it...
15:
Yeah, that's exactly why I plan to
have a professional lockpick look at
it.
18: I think the shop is over this way!
23:
Hi there. Are you Keyana, by any
chance? We have a lock we'd like
you to pick for us.
28:
Oh, you must be Alk! I heard all
about you from Lilie!
31:
All right, where's the little fella that
needs opening?
35:
This one right here...
What do you think? Can you do it?
39:
Hmm, now this is a real peculiar one
you've found here... Where'd you
pick this up exactly? The lock is
pretty odd.
42:
I'm tempted to say it's defective...
but hey, that's the Kaleidoscope for
you! Never know what you're gonna
get!
47: So, do you think you can open it?
51:
Why, of course I can!
Leave it to me.
57:
Why exactly do we need to be in the
woods to open a little box?
63: Hehe... Just stand back and watch!
67:
Ring, ring, ring
By the sound of my bell
I bid you open up, little lock!
75:
You mean you unlocked it by just
ringing a bell?!
78:
Hehe, pretty cool, isn't it? With this
bell, I can open up any lock I find!
83:
That doesn't seem fair. Can you
really call it 'lockpicking' at that
point?
89: I can't believe it was that easy!
95:
Huh?
No, no, you can't open it yet!
108:
That's why I said to WAIT!
I unlocked it, but that doesn't mean I
disarmed the traps!
119:
The box transformed into a massive
treasure chest?!
130:
I see. You brought us outside the
town because you foresaw the
possibility of danger lurking within
the box.
134:
Exactly!
It's not uncommon for stuff I open to
explode, or release deadly gas or
something!
138:
At that point I'd rethink my line of
work...
140:
Haha, it's a tad on the dangerous
side, perhaps!
141:
Also, when you've got a bell that
opens any lock, people tend to be
suspicious of you. That's why I try not
to use it in Palpebra...
144:
I had a guy run into my shop the
other day, claiming I had tried to
open his strongbox!
149:
That really doesn't sound easy... I
don't know how you do it!
152:
Right, we haven't paid you for your
trouble. Would this be enough?
157:
Wh-what? That's a LOT of money.
Are you sure?
160:
Yep! Lilie told us that it's best if we
give a cut of the treasure we find.
This one was a huge haulyou
deserve to be compensated!
164:
If it hadn't been for you, we mighta
just smashed this thing open.
Just take the money!
170:
I can't believe it, I've never gotten
this much from a client before...
Thank you!
172:
All I did was ring my bell, though!
Seriously, it was super simple!
175:
You guys are THE BEST customers
ever!
178:
Say, would you guys be willing to
hire me?
182: You want to work for us full-time?
186:
Yes, exactly! If I'm by your side, you'll
be able to open any chests you find
right on the spot!
192:
We would really appreciate your aid.
That being said, ours is a dangerous
journey.
195:
You don't need to tell me, I was right
here when you fought those
monsters! I'm no stranger to danger!
198:
But forget all that, I just REALLY want
to come along with you guys all of a
sudden!
204:
You make decisions very fast, don't
you?
Hmm, that being said, I don't see
any problem with it!
209:
Me neither.
Welcome to the group, Keyana.
213: Looking forward to working with you!
223:
I promise you WON'T regret hiring
me!
